text:
Starting from the building named "signature", take your time to walk up the stream, past an aqueduct until the end. There is a good area for plane spotting.
Unfortunately, the bridges are sealed off and cannot be crossed, and there are few planes landing and taking off these days. Instead, it's now quiet and tranquil.
Continue on to sutd singapore University of technology and design n have a nice economical lunch at the canteen.
A strip of greeneries in the middle of business area. The 'tunnel' below the road crossing is quite interesting.
Just be careful in the mornings, there are one or two fellows who seem to be mentally unsound who will soak in the sun at certain locations. Sharing to just be mindful and avoid them.

Quite a big business park with small little "garden" in between building... There's a "big" garden with bridge to relax too thou, could just sit to see aeroplanes go up n down "every single minute" at the side... Business park nearby Changi city mall/ Expo / expo MRT/ SUTD/ Hotels/ (little) bus station etc...
Nice Spotting Place, bring snacks as there are not any stores very close by. A camera with roughly 170mm zoom is optimal.
